Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *AI Product Engineer* position with *Guidewire*. I bring over three years of professional experience building AI-powered systems, multi-agent orchestration platforms, and RAG architectures, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade AI systems that directly reflect *the unique intersection of engineering depth and product intuition this position demands*. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph that decomposes complex workflows into agentic tasks — exactly the kind of system Guidewire needs to transform static insurance forms into dynamic, agentic workflows. I built rapid prototyping frameworks that translate natural-language intents into production-ready tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints, demonstrating the ability to move from "What if..." to working demo in days, not months. To ensure these AI systems were production-ready for regulated environments, I designed evaluation frameworks using LangSmith and Langfuse to measure accuracy, latency, and reliability across thousands of scenarios, and engineered RAG architectures with vector databases and context-aware prompt routing to minimize hallucinations — reducing latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50%. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I built an internal chatbot using LangChain and RAG with PostgreSQL vector store, implementing retrieval-augmented generation over documentation to reduce ticket resolution time by 20%. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications in regulated environments — giving me direct experience building mission-critical systems that customers trust in highly regulated industries. Together, these roles have prepared me to *design agentic workflows, own the eval loop, and bridge the gap between the Art of the Possible and the Reality of the Regulated* — exactly what the Guidewire Product organization needs.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in AI model development, GPU-accelerated computing, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into *the rationality, curiosity, and collegiality that Guidewire culture values*. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on the Pace HPC cluster, implementing GPU-accelerated model training pipelines for generative AI in regulated design workflows. I deployed production inference using vLLM and Hugging Face, architecting secure model serving infrastructure that balances performance with compliance requirements — demonstrating the ability to navigate the constraints of regulated environments without sacrificing innovation. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph, for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex, non-deterministic AI concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring *the technical translation and cross-functional collaboration this role demands*. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who prototypes with speed, evaluates with rigor, and communicates with clarity — all of which I would bring to *the Guidewire mission of reimagining the \$2 trillion P&C insurance industry as AI-native*.

I have always been passionate about *enabling innovation in regulated industries and building AI systems that customers can trust*, and I envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of *the Guidewire mission to provide a trusted platform for insurers to engage, innovate, and grow efficiently*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

